OL,3,COnboard the fully autonomous boat that
OL,4,Ccould save lives at sea
OL,6,FITV News Health and Science
OL,7,FCorrespondent Martin Stew steps aboard
OL,8,Fan uncrewed autonomous boat with its
OL,9,Fown brain
OL,11,FIn the shadow of Britain's biggest
OL,12,Fwarship, we were given a first look at
OL,13,Fwhat the future could hold for naval
OL,14,Foperations.
OL,16,FA boat with a brain of its own.
OL,18,FHere, on the Solent, BAE Systems -
OL,19,Fwhich is most known for its work in
OL,20,Fthe air - is developing a fully
OL,21,Fautonomous craft for the seas.
